From: "Perhaps a Princess..." <sarah@...>

On Mon, 23 Aug 1999, Greg McTague wrote:

> From: Greg McTague <gmctague@...>
>
> Bahhh..by Karana's tears, i do so LOVE listening to the mushroom picking
> Dark Elves speak about all their gods' death and evil, when they often
find
> themselves compromising their beliefs by joining and depending on the
> lighter parties for survival.

Ah. Our God Innoruk does not forbid us from using you guys when the result
is destruction and death more than we could do on our own. Sometimes it is
even His will that we heal you that you might serve his purposes longer
before
you die.

If you do not serve Innoruk, then do not presume to understand his will.
